                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d812">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">714.1515/973: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Chargé in Guatemala</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Hawks</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Guatemala</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1929-11-13T12:00:00-06:00"
                            >November 13, 1929—noon</date>.<lb/>[Received 3:35 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>146. Referring to Department’s telegram of November 12, 5 p.m.<note n="43"
                        xml:id="d812fn43">See footnote 42.</note>
                </p>
                <p>The Minister for Foreign Affairs has informed me that it will be convenient for
                    Guatemala to have the conference convened on December <pb facs="1106" n="970"
                        xml:id="pg_970"/> 15th. The Guatemalan delegation will consist of Carlos
                    Salazar as delegate and Carlos Salazar, Junior, and Silva Pena as
                    secretaries.</p>
                <p>Repeated to Honduras.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hawks</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
